Mouche Phillips (born 1973) is an Australian actress and theatre producer, best known for her television roles as Aviva "Viv" Newton in Home and Away (1989–90) and Eva Sykes in police procedural series Water Rats (2000–01).

Phillips was born in Sydney, and attended Woollahra Public School with several other future actors, including Home and away co-star Justine Clarke and singer Deni Hines, and then St Catherine's School, Waverley from 1984 to 1989.
Phillips began her career in 1985 by playing the character of Jackie Wilson in the children's television show Butterfly Island.
She then starred as "Beatie Bow" in the 1986 feature film Playing Beatie Bow when she was twelve years old.
On 5 July 1989, she premiered as a cast member of the popular series Home and Away, on which she played Aviva "Viv" Newton.
She left the series on 25 May 1990.
She later starred in a number of the Kennedy Miller Productions in the 1980s.
In 2000, Phillips appeared as a guest in the police series Water Rats where she played Eva Minton-Sykes, wife of Gavin Sykes until 2001.
